icana feminist canon to reveal how queer gender variance has always been crucial to this literary tradition.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 21. Dez 2019) 4aAdelina Anthony. 4aChicana. 4aChicano. 4aChicanx. 4aFelicia Luna Lemus. 4aGloria Anzaldua. 4aHelena Maria Viramontes. 4aJovita Gonzalez. 4abinary. 4abutch. 4afemale. 4afeminist. 4agender queerness. 4agender. 4aidentity. 4alesbian. 4aliterary. 4aliterature. 4amasculine. 4aqueer. 4asex. 4atransgender. 4avariance. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018z978311066330308iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package 2017-2018z978311065742508iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertRUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018z978311066608340uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780813594569423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780813594569.jpg  a978-3-11-065742-5  RUP eBook-Package 2017-2018c2017d2018  a978-3-11-066330-3  RUP Pilot eBook-Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  a978-3-11-066608-3  RUP eBook-Package Frontlist 2018b2018  aEBA_CL_LT  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_LT  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA14ALL  aPDA16SSH  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA1ALL  aPDA2  aPDA2HUM  aPDA5EBK  aPDA7ENG